OL,1,D]S737{kkkc5FPeople 'need to accept'    
OL,2,D]S555{jjj25Fthey're poorer, says Bank  
OL,3,D]Suuu{rrzq5F                           
OL,4,T#######################################
OL,5, The Bank of England's top economist has
OL,6, said people in the UK need to accept   
OL,7, that they are poorer otherwise prices  
OL,8, will continue to rise.                 
OL,10,FHuw Pill told a podcast in the US that 
OL,11,Fthere was a "reluctance to accept that,
OL,12,Fyes, we're all worse off".             
OL,14,FHe said in response to higher bills and
OL,15,Fother costs rising, workers had        
OL,16,Fresponded by asking for wage increases 
OL,17,Fand businesses were charging more.     
OL,19,FUK inflation, the rate of which prices 
OL,20,Frises, was 10.1% in the year to March. 
